LOTR - Conquest calls cellSaveDataUserAutoLoad on a directory that doesn't exist and throws access violation when reading memory upon calling  ```funcFile(ppu, result, fileGet, fileSet);```on savedata_op

The game used to work before, so this is a regression

Adding a sanity check on cellSaveDataUserAutoLoad before calling savedata_op solves the issue
```
const std::string base_dir = vfs::get(fmt::format("/dev_hdd0/home/%08u/savedata/", userId ? userId : 1u));
std::string dir_path = base_dir + dirName.get_ptr() + "/";

// Check if the directory exists first
// LOTR - Conquest calls cellSaveDataUserAutoLoad on a directory that doesn't exist
if (!fs::is_dir(vfs::get(dir_path))) 
{
    return CELL_SAVEDATA_ERROR_FAILURE;
}
```

Although I'm pretty sure the fix is correct, I'm also pretty sure this is not the way to go, and that it should be fixed within savedata_op itself.
_Note: I've also tested this with #3918 and the issue persists._

@jjsat Any ideas?

